Namespace GoogleMapsWrapper.Elements

Classes

GoogleMapElement

An abstract base class that contains properties from which map elements derive. A GoogleMapElement can be defined as a geo-locational data type, such as a map, marker (placemark), or polyline (path) that is leveraged by the wrapper.

Map

Defines a 'map' object and it's characteristics. It is primarily used as a parameter for methods within the StaticMapsApi.

Marker

Defines a marker (placemark) object and it's characteristics. It is primarily used as parameter to methods within the StaticMapsApi.
